Inception: The Start of Your Splunk App Development Career
------------------------------------------------------------

Inception was a Splunk App I created as part of my presentation at .conf19. It's a Splunk App for making Splunk Apps... trippy!

------------------------------------------------------------

Inception is designed to be used as a template for building your first Splunk App. Download the Inception.tar.gz from the Splunkbase, and extract the Inception directory. 

You can/should/must experiment with Inception by:

  1.) Modifying the dashboard views that are found in Inception/default/data/ui/views

  2.) Modifying the dashboard Javascript code that's found in Inception/appserver/static

  3.) Modifying the Python code that's found in Inception/bin

  4.) Create your own Perl scripts in Inception/bin if you're a masochist

------------------------------------------------------------

Developer Hints:

- You'll ideally want to edit Inception/default/app.conf, changing the id, label, and author info as appropriate for your own cleverly-named Splunk App!

- Make sure you're using a browser or browser extension that disables JavaScript and CSS caching so that all changes you make are actually reflected in your browser
 
- When you're building a Splunk App, it's helpful to create a script that copies your app to your Splunk server and restarts the Splunk Web UI so that your changes take effect


Please Note: The code editors on the page are for display purposes only. They're not interactive and cannot be used to update the code found on the page - no matter how much you might want them to.

------------------------------------------------------------

